comments.body:
Ok I will go a long with this for now, but I agree with Matt that we need to do a little more testing.
@giuseppe Have you looked at all of the other commands to see how well they handle this?

If I create this container, does podman images, podman ps, podman mount, podman rm, podman top ... work well with these containers?

@rhatdan @giuseppe @nalind 

If you want, I could work on using `umoci` as a storage driver rather than using `vfs` in a user namespace. The reason why this would be useful is that you don't need to use any user namespaces for the unpacking of the image -- **and** you automatically get support for the `user.rootlesscontainers` `xattr`.

I can send you an email with more details for what it would look like if you're interested. Obviously you don't have to block this PR on that, but it would mean that `--rootfs` wouldn't be necessary and you could explode images using `umoci` in rootless mode.

@rhatdan Yes it was broken very recently with some rootless changes (see opencontainers/runc#1819).

> If you can get umoci into containers/storage I would be all for it.

Awesome, I will shoot an email to @nalind and add you to cc to make sure we agree how the integration should work.
